olive oil
2 clove garlic
1 onion
1 carrot
1 packet pork mince
1 sachet Louisiana spice blend
6 Mini Flour Tortillas
1 packet Shredded Cheddar Cheese
1 tomato
1 cucumber
1 drizzle white wine vinegar
1 packet sour cream

• Preheat oven to 220°C/200°C fan-forced. Finely chop garlic and brown onion. Grate carrot.

• Heat a large frying pan over a high heat with a drizzle of olive oil. Cook pork mince, onion and carrot, breaking mince up with a spoon, until just browned, 4-5 minutes.
• Add garlic and Louisiana spice blend and cook, stirring, until fragrant, 1 minute.

TIP: Add a splash of water if the mixture looks dry!

• Arrange mini flour tortillas over a lined oven tray. Divide pork mixture between tortillas, spooning it onto one half of each tortilla, then top with shredded Cheddar cheese.
• Fold the empty half of each tortilla over to enclose filling and press down with a spatula. Brush (or spray) tortillas with a drizzle of olive oil, then season with salt and pepper.
• Bake quesadillas until cheese has melted and tortillas are golden, 10-12 minutes. Spoon any overflowing filling back into the quesadillas.
• Meanwhile, roughly chop tomato and cucumber. In a medium bowl, combine tomato, cucumber and a drizzle of white wine vinegar and olive oil. Season to taste.

• Divide Southern cheesy pork quesadillas between plates.
• Serve with cucumber salsa and a dollop of sour cream.